  "title": "M&E Manager (Office based) (Up to $10000 / 5 days / City Hall)",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: M&E Manager (Office based) (ID6041)<br />Location: City Hall<br />Working Hours: Mon-Fri 8:30AM-5:30PM<br />Salary: $8500-$10000<br /><br />Roles & Responsibilities<br />• Manage and oversee all M&E works to ensure compliance with standards, codes, safety regulations, and project timelines.<br />• Coordinate with clients, consultants, authorities, subcontractors, and site teams to resolve technical issues and ensure smooth project execution.<br />• Lead submission and approval of M&E shop drawings, material submissions, and method statements in line with project schedules.<br />• Supervise and guide M&E staff, supervisors, and subcontractors to ensure quality workmanship per approved drawings and specifications.<br />• Review technical specifications, drawings, and design intent; issue RFIs and resolve discrepancies with consultants/clients.<br />• Monitor site progress, inspections, variation orders, and troubleshoot M&E issues during construction and DLP stage.<br />• Manage M&E meetings and participate in Design & Build projects with consultants and architects.<br /><br />Requirement<br />• Degree or equivalent qualified<br />• Around 15 years working for a main contractor or subcontractor</p>",
